100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 21, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe following World War I. In the United States, the Senate continued its debate on the proposed tariff bill, sparking fierce political discourse. Meanwhile, in Egypt, nationalist sentiments grew as protests against British rule gained momentum, highlighting the country's struggle for independence.
